I mean, I learned firsthand that, so we, yeah, in 2000, I think seven,

00:13:09.800 --> 00:13:15.280
I've realized that if you put a door on the internet and you expose an IP address for anyone to use, right?

00:13:15.280 --> 00:13:22.840
Then we ended up with scenarios where you had like loads of hacking attempts from China trying to kind of like pwn the door because they just saw it as an IP address.

00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:27.440
